cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel training policy for neural networks that leverages multiple phases of the previous training process to guide later training updates. The paper presents comprehensive experimental results across a range of vision and NLP tasks, indicating that the proposed method is effective. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
